Friendswood & Bay Area

     * Traffic backs up at the intersection of FM 2351 and FM 518 in
       Friendswood. Proposition D in the city of Friendswood's Nov. 5 bond
       referendum proposes to provide funds to build a turn lane and a
       storage lane at this intersection as well as for various other
       transportation-related projects.
    Friendswood Prop D would fund mobility projects
     * Friendswood resident Michelle Thompson examines plans to revitalize
       the city's downtown during a meeting hosted by the Friendswood
       Downtown Economic Development Corp. last year. A $3.5 million
       project by the Texas Department of Transportation to build new
       downtown sidewalks might be an opportunity for the city to
       construct additional improvements including street and pedestrian
       lighting that are part of the Downtown Improvement Plan.
    TxDOT plans $3.4 million Friendswood sidewalk project
